<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="ida82fc6e8-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5" identifier="/us/usc/t10/s933"><num value="933">§ 933.</num><heading> Art. 133. Conduct unbecoming an officer</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Any commissioned officer, cadet, or midshipman who is convicted of conduct unbecoming an officer shall be punished as a court-martial may direct.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="ida82fc6e9-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5">(<ref href="/us/act/1956-08-10/ch1041">Aug. 10, 1956, ch. 1041</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/70A/76">70A Stat. 76</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/117/81/dA/tV/s542/a">Pub. L. 117–81, div. A, title V, § 542(a)</ref>, <date date="2021-12-27">Dec. 27, 2021</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/135/1709">135 Stat. 1709</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
